itialize","content":"This sets up the data branch and writes .hyper-pm/config.json. You can override branch name and remote later; see Configuration."},"290":{"id":"/getting-started/quickstart-8","page_id":"/getting-started/quickstart","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/quickstart#create-work-items","content":"Use --format text (a global option before the subcommand) for human-readable tables during exploration:"},"291":{"id":"/getting-started/quickstart-9","page_id":"/getting-started/quickstart","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/quickstart#next-steps","content":"Turn on GitHub sync and set GITHUB_REPO — see GitHub sync."},"292":{"id":"/getting-started/quickstart-10","page_id":"/getting-started/quickstart","type":"text","url":"/getting-started/quickstart#next-steps","content":"Start coding from a ticket with hyper-pm ticket work --id … — see Tickets."},"293":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"page","content":"GitHub sync","url":"/integrations/github-sync"},"294":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-0","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync","content":"Outbound and full inbound sync, labels, planning JSON, and PR activity."},"295":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-1","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"Modes"},"296":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-2","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#outbound-behavior","content":"Outbound behavior"},"297":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-3","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#inbound-full","content":"Inbound (full)"},"298":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-4","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Issue creation vs update"},"299":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-5","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"Assignees"},"300":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-6","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"Configuration (and global --sync) selects how much network integration runs:"},"301":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-7","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"off — no GitHub API work."},"302":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-8","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"outbound — push hyper-pm changes to issues."},"303":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-9","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#modes","content":"full — outbound plus inbound comparison and optional PR timeline ingestion for eligible tickets."},"304":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-10","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#outbound-behavior","content":"Issue labels include hyper-pm, ticket, plus each ticket label (GitHub’s label length limits apply)."},"305":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-11","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#outbound-behavior","content":"Ticket planning (priority, size, estimate, schedule) is embedded in a fenced JSON block after the issue body so full inbound can round-trip fields conservatively (only keys present in the fence participate — older issues without keys are not mass-cleared)."},"306":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-12","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#inbound-full","content":"Compares non-reserved labels and the planning JSON fence to the local projection and appends GithubInboundUpdate when something differs."},"307":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-13","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#inbound-full","content":"After inbound, for tickets in_progress with linked issues, hyper-pm may load linked PR timelines when bodies reference issues with Refs / Closes / Fixes — appending GithubPrActivity events. This issues extra GitHub API calls per linked PR."},"308":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-14","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Creates on GitHub only happen for tickets with a valid epic + story chain."},"309":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-15","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Tickets without a story are skipped for creation until you attach --story."},"310":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-16","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#issue-creation-vs-update","content":"Tickets that already have a githubIssueNumber are still updated when unlinked (the issue body drops parent ids until you link again)."},"311":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-17","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"Tickets store at most one assignee (GitHub login). Outbound sync sets that user as the issue’s assignee (additional assignees on the issue may be removed). Inbound reads the first assignee when GitHub returns several."},"312":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-18","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"type: warn"},"313":{"id":"/integrations/github-sync-19","page_id":"/integrations/github-sync","type":"text","url":"/integrations/github-sync#assignees","content":"Sync skips entirely when you pass sync run --no-github, when sync is off in config, or when GitHub credentials are missing."},"314":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"page","content":"MCP server (hyper-pm-mcp)","url":"/integrations/mcp-server"},"315":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-0","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"Model Context Protocol stdio server wrapping the hyper-pm CLI."},"316":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-1","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#build-order","content":"Build order"},"317":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-2","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#tool-hyper_pm_run","content":"Tool: hyper_pm_run"},"318":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-3","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"Environment"},"319":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-4","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#publishing","content":"Publishing"},"320":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-5","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#cursor-example","content":"Cursor example"},"321":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-6","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"The hyper-pm-mcp app exposes hyper-pm over MCP using a stdio transport."},"322":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-7","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"type: warn"},"323":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-8","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server","content":"hyper_pm_run executes the same hyper-pm process you would run in a shell. Only enable this MCP server in trusted editor configurations."},"324":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-9","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#build-order","content":"From the monorepo root:"},"325":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-10","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#build-order","content":"Register the server with node and the absolute path to apps/hyper-pm-mcp/dist/main.mjs."},"326":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-11","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#tool-hyper_pm_run","content":"argv (required): tokens after global options, e.g. [\"epic\", \"read\"] or [\"doctor\"]."},"327":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-12","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#tool-hyper_pm_run","content":"Optional fields mirror CLI globals (cwd, repo, tempDir, actor, githubRepo, dataBranch, remote, sync, keepWorktree)."},"328":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-13","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#tool-hyper_pm_run","content":"--format json is always injected. The response is JSON text with exitCode, streams, and parsedStdout when stdout is valid JSON."},"329":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-14","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"See apps/hyper-pm-mcp/env.example and @workspace/env. Notable:"},"330":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-15","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#environment","content":"HYPER_PM_CLI_PATH — absolute path to main.cjs when package resolution is insufficient."},"331":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-16","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#publishing","content":"When publishing to npm, publish hyper-pm first, then hyper-pm-mcp, using pnpm publish from each app so workspace: ranges rewrite correctly. Details in apps/hyper-pm-mcp/README.md."},"332":{"id":"/integrations/mcp-server-17","page_id":"/integrations/mcp-server","type":"text","url":"/integrations/mcp-server#cursor-example","content":"Replace the path with the real location on your machine."},"333":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"page","content":"Web UI (hyper-pm-web)","url":"/integrations/web-ui"},"334":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-0","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui","content":"Local browser UI that wraps the hyper-pm CLI bundle."},"335":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-1","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#security-defaults","content":"Security defaults"},"336":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-2","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#run-locally","content":"Run locally"},"337":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-3","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#build-the-cli","content":"Build the CLI"},"338":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-4","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#configure-optional","content":"Configure (optional)"},"339":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-5","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#start-the-app","content":"Start the app"},"340":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-6","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"heading","url":"/integrations/web-ui#http-api","content":"HTTP API"},"341":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-7","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui","content":"hyper-pm-web serves a small local UI around the same hyper-pm/dist/main.cjs binary the CLI uses, so behavior stays aligned."},"342":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-8","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#security-defaults","content":"type: warn"},"343":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-9","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#security-defaults","content":"Defaults to 127.0.0.1 — see HYPER_PM_WEB_HOST. Do not expose the dev server to untrusted networks without TLS and authentication."},"344":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-10","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#security-defaults","content":"--repo, --temp-dir, and --format are chosen by the server; clients cannot override them through argv."},"345":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-11","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#security-defaults","content":"Optional HYPER_PM_WEB_TOKEN: when set, POST /api/run requires Authorization: Bearer <token>."},"346":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-12","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#configure-optional","content":"See apps/hyper-pm-web/README.md and root packages/env/env.example. Common variables include HYPER_PM_WEB_REPO (repo root for --repo, defaulting to server cwd), HYPER_PM_WEB_TEMP_DIR (worktree parent or ephemeral temp cleaned on shutdown), plus HYPER_PM_WEB_HOST, HYPER_PM_WEB_PORT, and HYPER_PM_WEB_TOKEN."},"347":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-13","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#start-the-app","content":"From the Git repo you want to manage (so default --repo is correct):"},"348":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-14","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#start-the-app","content":"Or production-style build then start."},"349":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-15","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#start-the-app","content":"Open the printed URL (default http://127.0.0.1:3847)."},"350":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-16","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#http-api","content":"GET /api/health — { ok, repoPath, tempDirParent }"},"351":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-17","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#http-api","content":"POST /api/run — JSON body compatible with @workspace/hyper-pm-cli-runner input, except repo and tempDir in argv are ignored or forbidden; the server merges configured paths."},"352":{"id":"/integrations/web-ui-18","page_id":"/integrations/web-ui","type":"text","url":"/integrations/web-ui#http-api","content":"GitHub sync and other features use the same environment variables as the CLI."},"353":{"id":"/intro/architecture","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"page","content":"Architecture","url":"/intro/architecture"},"354":{"id":"/intro/architecture-0","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture","content":"How the data branch, JSONL log, worktrees, and projections fit together."},"355":{"id":"/intro/architecture-1","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"heading","url":"/intro/architecture#high-level-flow","content":"High-level flow"},"356":{"id":"/intro/architecture-2","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"heading","url":"/intro/architecture#repository-layout-conceptual","content":"Repository layout (conceptual)"},"357":{"id":"/intro/architecture-3","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"heading","url":"/intro/architecture#event-sourcing-mindset","content":"Event sourcing mindset"},"358":{"id":"/intro/architecture-4","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"heading","url":"/intro/architecture#sync-as-a-side-channel","content":"Sync as a side channel"},"359":{"id":"/intro/architecture-5","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"heading","url":"/intro/architecture#wrappers-share-one-binary","content":"Wrappers share one binary"},"360":{"id":"/intro/architecture-6","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#high-level-flow","content":"init creates or adopts an orphan branch (no parent commit) that holds hyper-pm data, and writes .hyper-pm/config.json in your working tree."},"361":{"id":"/intro/architecture-7","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#high-level-flow","content":"Most mutating commands run against a temporary Git worktree checked out at the data branch, append one or more lines to the event log, commit, and optionally push — your primary branch is untouched."},"362":{"id":"/intro/architecture-8","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#high-level-flow","content":"Reads replay the log (with schema versioning) into an in-memory projection of epics, stories, tickets, and sync cursors."},"363":{"id":"/intro/architecture-9","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#repository-layout-conceptual","content":"Exact filenames on the data branch are owned by the CLI implementation; treat them as opaque except through supported commands."},"364":{"id":"/intro/architecture-10","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#event-sourcing-mindset","content":"Think of the JSONL file as an append-only journal:"},"365":{"id":"/intro/architecture-11","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#event-sourcing-mindset","content":"Each line is a typed event (for example TicketCreated, GithubInboundUpdate)."},"366":{"id":"/intro/architecture-12","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#event-sourcing-mindset","content":"Deleting entities is modeled as soft deletes via events, not rm on rows."},"367":{"id":"/intro/architecture-13","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#event-sourcing-mindset","content":"doctor validates that the log can be read and replayed; use it in CI or before releases if you rely on automation."},"368":{"id":"/intro/architecture-14","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#sync-as-a-side-channel","content":"GitHub is a projection target, not the source of truth for hyper-pm’s core model. Outbound sync updates issues; inbound sync (full mode) translates issue changes back into events when they differ from what hyper-pm last wrote."},"369":{"id":"/intro/architecture-15","page_id":"/intro/architecture","type":"text","url":"/intro/architecture#wrappers-share-one-binary","content":"hyper-pm-web and hyper-pm-mcp spawn the same bundled CLI (dist/main.cjs) that you would run in a shell. That keeps UI, agents, and scripts aligned — there is no second implementation of business rules in the web layer."},"370":{"id":"/intro/overview","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"page","content":"Overview","url":"/intro/overview"},"371":{"id":"/intro/overview-0","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview","content":"What hyper-pm is for, how it stores data in Git, and when to use GitHub sync."},"372":{"id":"/intro/overview-1","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"heading","url":"/intro/overview#what-hyper-pm-is","content":"What hyper-pm is"},"373":{"id":"/intro/overview-2","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"heading","url":"/intro/overview#what-it-is-not","content":"What it is not"},"374":{"id":"/intro/overview-3","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"heading","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"Interfaces"},"375":{"id":"/intro/overview-4","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"heading","url":"/intro/overview#optional-github-issues-sync","content":"Optional GitHub Issues sync"},"376":{"id":"/intro/overview-5","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"heading","url":"/intro/overview#ai-assisted-fields","content":"AI-assisted fields"},"377":{"id":"/intro/overview-6","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-hyper-pm-is","content":"hyper-pm is a Git-native project manager: epics, stories, tickets, comments, and sync metadata live in your repository on a dedicated data branch, not only in a SaaS database. The CLI (and anything that wraps it) mutates state by appending typed events to a JSONL log and replaying them to build the current projection."},"378":{"id":"/intro/overview-7","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-hyper-pm-is","content":"That design gives you:"},"379":{"id":"/intro/overview-8","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-hyper-pm-is","content":"Offline-first workflows after clone and fetch — no hosted PM required for local reads and writes."},"380":{"id":"/intro/overview-9","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-hyper-pm-is","content":"Reviewable history of who changed what, suitable for compliance-minded teams."},"381":{"id":"/intro/overview-10","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-hyper-pm-is","content":"Disposable worktrees for mutations so your main checkout stays clean while the tool edits the data branch."},"382":{"id":"/intro/overview-11","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-it-is-not","content":"A full replacement for GitHub Projects, Jira workflows, or cross-repo portfolio views out of the box."},"383":{"id":"/intro/overview-12","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#what-it-is-not","content":"A multi-tenant hosted service: security and backups are your Git hosting and practices."},"384":{"id":"/intro/overview-13","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"Surface"},"385":{"id":"/intro/overview-14","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"Role"},"386":{"id":"/intro/overview-15","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"hyper-pm CLI"},"387":{"id":"/intro/overview-16","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"Canonical API: init, CRUD on epics/stories/tickets, work, comment, sync, audit, doctor, repo helpers."},"388":{"id":"/intro/overview-17","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"hyper-pm-web"},"389":{"id":"/intro/overview-18","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"Local browser UI that shells the same CLI bundle; good for browsing and editing without memorizing flags."},"390":{"id":"/intro/overview-19","page_id":"/intro/overview","type":"text","url":"/intro/overview#interfaces","content":"hyp